\.TH man 1 "15 April 2021" "1.0" "Simple-shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- Linux shell program recreation that will provide the user with a user interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
$ ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
the simple_shell is a command line interpreter (a.k.a. "shell"), in the tradition of the first UNIX shell written by Ken Thompson in 1971. This shell is intentionally minimalistic, but includes the basic functionality of a *nix command line user interface.
.SH Compiling
gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror -pedantic *.c
.SH OPTION
Built-ins
.br
	env
- It will display the current environment
.br
	exit
- It will exit from the mini-shell.
.SH EXAMPLES
$ ls
.br
Display the list of files in the current dir
.br


$ /bin/pwd
.br
Displays display the current directory address
.br

$ exit or Ctrl + D
.br
Exits from the shell.
.SH ENVIRONMENT

Examples of Environment Variables

     PWD
               The current directory address
     ENV
               Display the environment variables.
               
.SH SEE ALSO
.I sh(1), execve(2), signal(2), exit(2), isatty(3).
.SH Bugs
No known bugs. Yet.
.SH AUTHOR
Raimundo Gallino - Jorge Tuset